t moment is unprecedented, highlighting the pivotal role of the classroom in contextualizing and responding to our perilous times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aRacexStudy and teaching (Higher)zUnited States. 0aRace-Study and teaching (Higher)-United States. 0aRacismxStudy and teaching (Higher)zUnited States. 0aRacism-Study and teaching (Higher)-United States. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : Higher Education. 4aEducation : Social Context of Education. 4aEducation : Teaching and Learning. 7aEDUCATION / Multicultural Education.2bisacsh1 aCohen, Jason E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMack, Dwayne A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRaynor, Sharon D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848227940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438482279423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438482279/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles